about.summary: Parses http request data in application/json, multipart/form-data, or application/x-www-form-urlencoded format. Includes example of hosting and parsing html form data in R using either 'httpuv' or 'Rhttpd'.

name: r-webutils
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-webutils
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/webutils_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/webutils/webutils_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 412f6ea0ae5572fa7872880832f8849b5d31f1937a412db55d927d28b3db1b4e

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-curl >=2.5
    - r-jsonlite
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-curl >=2.5
    - r-jsonlite

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('webutils')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('webutils')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jeroen/webutils
  license: MIT
  summary: Parses http request data in application/json, multipart/form-data, or application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    format. Includes example of hosting and parsing html form data in R using either
    'httpuv' or 'Rhttpd'.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
